The White House has announced that a Summit on Worker Voice will be held on October 7th. The summit aims to explore ways to ensure that working Americans are benefiting from economic growth. President Obama first mentioned the summit in March, highlighting the difficulties faced by working families in getting ahead despite economic recovery. The focus of the summit will be on how workers can have their voices heard in the workplace in a way that is beneficial for both workers and businesses. The labor movement, known for its role in strengthening the middle class, will be a key topic of discussion. The summit hopes to inspire a new generation of Americans to recognize the power of their voice in the workplace. More information about the summit will be released in the coming weeks.